//Locations Strings Palace Of The Parliament The Palace of The Parliament is the main attraction of Bucharest. Romanian Athenaeum Athenaeum is the symbol of Bucharest and it surely is an architectural gem. National Bank Of Romania Is one of the most imposing and massive bank edifices in Romania, nowadays a historic and a art monument. Arch Of Triumph Arch of Triumph is another reason why Bucharest deserves its entitling of “Little Paris”. KM 0 In front of the National Theatre, is situated a symbolic and deferential monument for the revolution from ’89. Old Town The Old Town part of Bucharest, also called Lipscani, before the birth of the city, was a commercial center full of life.
National History Museum Of Romania Considered the most important museum of the Romanian state, it has gone recently through a wide process of renewal. National Museum Of Natural History Over 2 million zoological, paleontological, geological and world ethnography pieces. Village Museum National Village Museum is one of the first ethnographic museum in the world. The Museum of the Romanian Peasant It is one of the most original expositions of cultural art and traditional objects not only from Romania, but from the entire Europe. National Museum Of Geology King Carol the 1st founded in 1906 one of the most beautiful museum of Earth Science from the east-central part of Europe.
Herastrau Park Herastrau Park is the biggest park of Bucharest. Cismigiu Park the Garden of Cismigiu is the oldest public garden from Bucharest and it is located in the city center. Opera Park Turn right after you get out from the Opera and relax a few minutes in the small park from here. Kiseleff Park Park Kiseleff, with Russian resonance was designed and named after the Russian brisk general Pavel Dmitrievici Kiseliov. IOR Park IOR Park is one of the biggest eastern parks and it is a must see place in Bucharest.
Hanul lui Manuc The last caravanserai in South Eastern Europe Caru\' cu bere The place itself is very beautiful, nice location, old space. Staff are in trational dress. Building is an old church. The Artist Fine dining remains something of a novelty concept in Bucharest, but elegantly understated The Artist. Beca\’s Kitchen Home-style cooking doesn’t come much better than at Beca’s Kitchen, a little family-run restaurant. Pukka Tukka The location isn’t the most exciting but that shouldn’t dissuade anyone from venturing to Pukka Tukka, a super organic food bar.
